department.info:
Homeopathy is a natural form of medicine used by over 200 million people worldwide to treat both acute and chronic conditions. Homeopathy is a system of medicine which is based on treating the individual with highly diluted substances given in mainly tablet form, which triggers the body's natural system of healing. It is based
on the principle of "like cures like". In other words, a substance taken in small amounts will cure the same
symptoms it causes if it were taken in large amounts. When used appropriately under the guidance of a qualified homeopath, they can be taken by people of all ages, including infants, children, adults and pregnant or breastfeeding women.

department.info:
Ayurveda is one of the world's oldest holistic healing systems. It is a form of Complementary and Alternative Medicine (CAM).
This holistic system aims to restore health by understanding the root cause of the disease, and not just the symptoms. It aims to maintain the wellbeing of a healthy individual and provide relief in a diseased individual. Ayurveda works with the person - body, mind, and soul. Whilst there are no side effects of Ayurvedic medicines, the Ayurvedic doctor plays a vital role in your
dosage.They will understand your persona, your lifestyle and the various physical and emotional balances involved before advising the treatment to you.
